(+): Add A Source : now has a few choices.
+ : Add repo
📋 : Copy enabled sources to clipboard for pasting into package managers.

If you want all of your sources even if not enabled. Use AutoLists , press its (+) to create your current enabled sources, then turn all on with the green button on top right. Use the (+)Add New Source button on the main page, then select 📋(Copy to clipboard).
Alive Status : Change how Check If Alive checks repo. (Alive Status)
Only active if Check If Alive is enabled.
Apply : Force Apply if your not sure.
BackBurners :
Added repo status.
BackBurners can be emailed via: Contact/Send Backups on the ⓘ Info page.
Check if Alive Status : Added to Settings, choose which type.
If repo was down but now live again, its switch handle will be green temporarily.
Read the -How To- Page in app.

v933.1510.0-x = 32 bit support for iOS 9.3.3 -> 15.1.0 etc.
Some features as listed below will never work on iOS 9 etc.
v1100.1620.0-x = 64bit support for iOS 11 -> 16.2.0 etc
All listed features should work.

Added (🔍N) to Quick Keys. (Return all Repos with keywords in Notes.)
Start a search using the 🔍 on the main page.
Type what to look for.
Press the (🔍N) Quick Key.
It will display only repositories containing the search criteria if found in the Notes section.
